                            <comment id="14466426" author="mingfai" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2009 15:31:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there was no problem in Groovy 1.5.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466523" author="jimwhite" created="Fri, 13 Feb 2009 15:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This strikes me as a blocker for 1.6.0 because it is a major regression and surely is not the intended behavior (because as Jochen says, he intends to fix it for the next point release).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While I realize we&apos;re all anxious to get a &quot;real&quot; release out there, an interesting phenomenon is that making the RC releases appears to be what it takes to prompt downstream users/developers/testers to try out the new versions of Groovy.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So perhaps an RC every week or two until there are no major issues is the way to get to a good final release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466411" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 14 Feb 2009 14:05:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the issue is now fixed in 1.7.x, 1.6.x and I added a testcase for 1.5.x... I did not yet add the change to 1.6.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
